  "title": "IT Support / Desktop Support (2026A011)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Industry: </strong>Medical Science Sector<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Central area<br /><strong>Schedule:</strong> Monday to Friday, 2 shifts (8am-5pm, 10am-7pm)<br /><strong>Skills:</strong> IT Support, Phone, Email and On-site<br /><br />This role will particularly handle one of their MNC clients providing IT End-User, Technical Support based at the main office located in the central part of Singapore.<br /><br />As an IT Support, this will provide first-line and extended support for their IT needs including (but not limited) desktop/laptop support, network maintenance, software & systems troubleshooting.<br /><br /><strong>Position Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Will provide day to day local\\remote desktop support, receive inbound calls, answer questions, troubleshoot and document steps performed to resolve challenges with hardware, software, and application issues in a ticketing system.</li><li>Will also facilitate customer resolution for calls and engage their supervisors to ensure operational consistency across within the IT Support Centre.</li><li>Primarily provide break fix, fault diagnosis and resolution to IT equipment.</li></ul><p><strong>Position Requiremnts:</strong></p><ul><li>Atleast Diploma education related to Information Technology field.</li><li>Knowledge in desktop, laptop, computer troubleshooting, PC configuration and basic networking architecture.</li><li>Experience using Windows OS and Mac OS applications.</li><li>Handle user creation, update, delete and change requests</li><li>Must be a team player and have excellent interpersonal communication skills.</li><li>Role will be working 5-days a week with 2 shifts (8am to 5pm; 10am to 7pm)</li></ul><p>We will consider all candidates but will prioritize those with relevant experience.<br /></p><p>Thank you!</p><p></p><p>Joseph Syho</p><p>Reg Number: R1108657</p><p>EA Licence No: 18C9079</p>",
